{{short description|website on celebrity finances}} {{infobox dot-com company | name=CelebrityNetWorth | logo=[[File:Celebrity Net Worth.png|Celebrity Net Worth|165px]] | logo_size= | logo_alt= | country = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], [[United States|U.S.]] | type=Private | key people = Alex Chan | current status = Online | founder=Brian Warner | founded = {{start date and age|2008|10}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whois.domaintools.com/celebritynetworth.com|title=CelebrityNetWorth.com WHOIS, DNS, & Domain Info - DomainTools|work=[[WHOIS]]|date= |accessdate=2016-09-20}}</ref> | employees = 11-50 (See LinkedIn entry) | alexa= 14,696 (March 2018) | website={{URL|http://www.celebritynetworth.com/}} }}
'''CelebrityNetWorth''' is a website which reports estimates of the total assets and financial activities of celebrities. It is operated by the company Corte Lodato LLC, founded by [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] Brian Warner in 2008.<ref name="cnw">{{cite web|title=Celebrity Net Worth|url=http://www.celebritynetworth.com/about-us/|website=CelebrityNetWorth|accessdate=30 April 2016|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="the outline" />
The site has been criticized for a lack of transparency for its calculations, with no way to verify the accuracy what CelebrityNetWorth reports.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/19/style/richest-celebrities-in-hollywood.html|title=The Big Secret of Celebrity Wealth (Is That No One Knows Anything)|access-date=2018-09-25|language=en}}</ref> Most content is written by freelance writers, rather than journalists or computer scientists to analyze data.<ref name=":0" />
==Activities== CelebrityNetWorth creates web pages that list a celebrity's name, biography, and estimates of net worth and salary. The site calculates net worth by "applying a proprietary algorithm" based on publicly available information and using financial analysts to review such results.{{Citation needed|date=May 2016}}
Warner has said of their estimates that "If we end up too far off, there is always some kind of backlash. There have been a handful cases when we’ve been proved to be off, and we’ve corrected it."<ref>{{cite web |last=meredithqz |url=http://qz.com/364156/7-questions-with-the-ceo-who-gets-paid-to-know-what-every-celebrity-is-worth/ |title=Seven questions with the CEO who gets paid to know what every celebrity is worth |work=Quartz |date=March 18, 2015 |accessdate=April 30, 2016 }}</ref>
The site provides news articles on financial transactions of celebrities such as the purchase of a home or lawsuits.<ref name="cnw" />
CelebrityNetWorth creates lists ranking wealthy individuals based upon their wealth. In 2012 the company compiled a list of the 25 richest people in history, adjusted for inflation, naming [[Musa I of Mali|King Mansa Musa]] of the [[Mali Empire]] at the top of the list.<ref>{{cite web| title=Who’s The Richest Person In History?| date=October 16, 2012| publisher=NPR| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=https://www.npr.org/2012/10/16/162993083/whos-the-richest-person-in-history}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=King Mansa Musa of Mali named richest person of all time| author=Erik Ortiz| date=October 18, 2012| publisher=New York Daily News| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/king-mansa-musa-named-richest-history-article-1.1186261}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Mansa Musa of Mali Named World's Richest Man of All Time; Gates And Buffet Also Make List| date=October 17, 2012| publisher=Huffington Post| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/17/mansa-musa-worlds-richest-man-all-time_n_1973840.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Website names obscure 14th century African king the richest person in history| date=October 17, 2012| publisher=FOX News| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/17/website-names-obscure-14th-century-african-king-richest-person-in-history/}}</ref> That same year, it created a list of the world's richest DJs,<ref>{{cite web| title=The 30 Richest DJs In The World| author=Tom Breihan| date=June 12, 2012| publisher=StereoGum| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=http://www.stereogum.com/1062921/the-30-richest-djs-in-the-world/news/}}</ref> and a survey which named [[Ringo Starr]] as the world's richest drummer.<ref>{{cite web| title=Ringo Starr Talks Paul, Meditation and Why He Loves L.A.| author=Steve Chagollan| date=January 28, 2014| publisher=Variety| accessdate=17 April 2015|url=https://variety.com/2014/music/news/ringo-starr-paul-mccartney-beatles-1201073353/}}</ref>
In 2014, [[Google]] requested permission from Warner to include CelebrityNetWorth's data in its [[Knowledge Graph]]. Warner declined. However, in February 2016, Google began using information from its [[search engine indexing|search index]] of CelebrityNetWorth to display [[Google Searchology#Featured snippets|featured snippets]] with net worths at the top of their [[search engine results page|search result pages]] for relevant queries. The featured snippets were positioned above the search results, including results for CelebrityNetWorth. As a result, CelebrityNetWorth's [[web traffic]] declined by 65 percent from January 2016 to January 2017.<ref name="the outline">{{cite web|last1=Jeffries|first1=Adrianne|title=How Google eats a business whole|url=https://theoutline.com/post/1399/how-google-ate-celebritynetworth-com|website=The Outline|accessdate=12 Jul 2018|date=17 Apr 2017}}</ref>
